<div class="center">

== Description ==

Level 778 is an infinite, open woodland, shrouded in a thick, puffy lavender mist that disorients vision and devours light. The mist is the first impression guests will have upon arrival at the level, shrouding everything in yellowish purple that seeps into trees, ground, and any object caught in its relentless grasp.
{{Blurimage|file=LEVELFOTO77.png|caption=LEVEL PHOTO.|hovertext=PURPLE.}}
Visibility is only at a mere five meters. The fog has the nearly-whispering texture, piling up on purpose to conceal what lies ahead. There are no natural sounds no wind, no animals but the muffled sound of one's own footsteps. Those who tarry long enough speak of hearing reed thin, muffled whispers in the fog, though no one has ever been able to follow them back to their origin.

The only way to pierce the fog is with Hasselblad 500CM cameras, which are positioned throughout the forest in states of deconstruction. The cameras flash images of unrecognizable forms through their lenses, but the image that they offer is black and unpredictable. Working cameras imported from other levels are not possible any other camera imported into the level will not work at all. It is understood that whatever the reason might be which enables the Hasselblad lenses to achieve this, its function is one of the mysteries of this magnitude.

In the distance, across the fog, is a collection of weathered buildings. Walkways, courtyards, and chambers, too large to exist from the inside, connect the buildings. The land has no charted map, as buildings and trees have been known to move out of range. Compasses don't function, and marks on bark rot within hours.
{{Blurimage|file=fotoahh.jpg|caption=LEVEL PHOTO 2.|hovertext=PURPLE.|align=Left}}
Few have entered these structures, but anecdotally they report them to be inhabited. The occupants within do not present themselves but instead vanish into the fog or wait until the point of attack. Nothing can be known for certain of their breed, but legends speak of ill defined shadowy figures, with slow unseen actions on the fringes of consciousness. They believe that the creature's density is much stronger inside the buildings and that the supposedly safe space becomes a zone of death.

The [[Phenomenon 15]] takes up the entire floor, and it is literally impossible for there to be anything other than a single human there at any given time. Even if a couple of them arrive at the same time, they will all be completely alone. Voices, lights, or any other sign of other adventurers simply vanish into the mist. There's no explanation why this has been found, but it's thought that the level itself produces the illusion or distorts space to trap each player.

There is no air, and no provisions inside. There is water located inside the forest that is filled with a purple color, metallic taste, and unwholesome effect. Provisions are not available, and adventurers will explore further inside the level hoping to get provisions an action that almost always leads to disappearing.

The experience is recalled in shattered coherence. Memories of what they saw wither with time, as though the level wipes its mark. Those which survive are tainted with paranoia, confusion, and an incessant feeling that something was there but in no manner understood.

== Entities ==

The Shadows are entities found within the level, characterized by their uncharacterizable physical nature. They appear usually as black silhouettes that resemble human forms, but any attempt to understand what they really are is futile. The creatures have extremely violent patterns of behavior, usually hunting in pairs of two or three or by themselves.

The Shadows use the dense fog on the level to launch quick ambushes and hence become even more dangerous. Despite numerous attempts by the [[A.A.E.G.]] to reach out to these creatures, every attempt except one has been unsuccessful. The Shadows are always aggressive, and therefore the [[A.A.E.G.]] issue threats rather than make further attempts at contact. Regions where Shadows are most commonly found are also teeming with [[False Grass]], a deadly environmental hazard that impedes movement and survival.

== Colonies & Outposts ==

Due to the conditions it is impossible to have a base at the level.

== Entrances ==

* Purple mist signals proximity to Level 778 in forest or water levels. It's dense, disorienting, and key to navigating the level's sectors.

== Exits ==

* The most known way to get out is to find a hidden theater among the buildings in the forest. Standing on the stage transports you to some level that is a theater.

* Alternatively, following a purple cloverfield path behind the theater will lead to [[Level 626.2]].
